{{BLP sources|date=October 2018}} {{third-party|date=October 2018}} {{short description|South African optometrist}} {{use dmy dates|date=September 2018}} {{use list-defined references|date=September 2018}} {{Use British English|date=September 2018}} {{Infobox academic | honorific_prefix = | name = Dennis M. Levi | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | gender = | native_name = | native_name_lang = | birth_name = | birth_date = | birth_place = South Africa{{r|press}} | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | region = | nationality = | citizenship = | residence = | other_names = | occupation = university professor | period = | known_for = | title = | boards = | spouse = | children = | parents = | relatives = | awards = | website = | education = | alma_mater = [[University of Houston]] | thesis_title = | thesis_url = | thesis_year = | school_tradition = | doctoral_advisor = | academic_advisors = | era = | discipline = [[vision science]] | sub_discipline = [[optometry]] | workplaces = {{ubl|[[University of Houston]]|{{nobreak|[[University of California, Berkeley]]}}}} | doctoral_students = | notable_students = | main_interests = | notable_works = | notable_ideas = | influenced = | signature = | signature_alt = | signature_size = | footnotes = }}
'''Dennis M. Levi''' is a South African [[optometrist]]. He is professor of optometry and [[vision science]] and a professor of [[neuroscience]] at the School of Optometry of the [[University of California, Berkeley|University of California]] at [[Berkeley, California|Berkeley]], in California in the United States.{{r|soo}} He is a former [[dean (academic)|dean]] of the same school, an appointment he took up in 2001.{{r|press}} He was previously the Cullen Distinguished Professor of Optometry on the faculty of the [[University of Houston]], in [[Houston, Texas]], where he also did his [[PhD]].{{r|press}} He is a [[fellow]] of the [[American Academy of Optometry]].{{r|aaopt}}
Levi has conducted significant research into [[amblyopia]].{{r|press}}
