'''Erythrodontia''' is the red discoloration of [[teeth]].<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://www.worldcat.org/oclc/700376882|title=Henry's clinical diagnosis and management by laboratory methods|last=Henry|first=John Bernard|date=2011|publisher=Elsevier/Saunders|others=McPherson, Richard A., Pincus, Matthew R.|year=|isbn=1437709745|edition= 22nd|location=Philadelphia, PA|pages=|oclc=700376882}}</ref> It can be seen in [[congenital erythropoietic porphyria]].
