{{Infobox academic|name=Keertan Dheda|image=|birth_date=March 1969|birth_place=Durban, South Africa|residence=Cape Town|nationality=South African|occupation=Researcher; Professor; Medical Doctor|known_for=Professor of Respiratory Medicine Scientific contributions to the field of TB and Respiratory Medicine|alma_mater=University of Witwatersrand, University College London,|discipline=Medicine|sub_discipline=Respiratory Medicine; Immunology; Antimicrobial Resistance; Tuberculosis|workplaces=University of Cape Town, University College of London, London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine}}
'''Keertan Dheda''' [<nowiki/>[[Bachelor of Medicine, Bachelor of Surgery|MBBCh]] (Wits), FCP(SA), FCCP, [[Doctor of Philosophy|PhD]] (Lond), [[Royal College of Physicians|FRCP]] (Lond)], born in March 1969, is a Professor of [[Pulmonology|Respiratory Medicine]], and Head of the Division of [[Pulmonology]] at the [[University of Cape Town]], which provides tertiary respiratory facilities to a population of 3.74 million people including for poverty-related diseases such as [[tuberculosis]], [[HIV]], [[pneumonia]], and other diseases including [[Chronic obstructive pulmonary disease|COPD]], [[asthma]] and [[lung cancer]]. He also holds an Honorary Professor appointment at the [[London School of Hygiene & Tropical Medicine|London School of Hygiene and Tropical Medicine]], and is a Visiting Professor at [[University College London]].
== Research ==
His research work focuses on the molecular epidemiology, diagnosis, transmission, and treatment of [[Tuberculosis|TB]], and antimicrobial resistance of pulmonary pathogens including ''[[Mycobacterium tuberculosis]]''.<ref name="Research work">{{cite web|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=Research work|url=http://lunginstitute.co.za/liiu|website=lunginstitute.co.za|publisher=University of Cape Town Lung Institute|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> He has a keen interest in medical education and interventional pulmonology including bronchial thermoplasty, ultrasound-guided mediastinal biopsy (EBUS TBNA) and medical thoracoscopy.
== Awards & Recognition == He has been the recipient of several prestigious awards, including the [[International Union Against Tuberculosis and Lung Disease]] Scientific Award,<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theunion.org/what-we-do/awards/the-union-scientific-prize|title=The Union Scientific Prize|work=The Union|access-date=2018-07-06|language=en}}</ref> the [[Harry Oppenheimer Fellowship Award]],<ref>{{Citation|title=Harry Oppenheimer Fellowship Award|date=2017-05-05|url=https://en.wikipedia.org/w/index.php?title=Harry_Oppenheimer_Fellowship_Award&oldid=778886038|work=Wikipedia|language=en|access-date=2018-07-06}}</ref> the [https://www.nstf.org.za/ NSTF] BHP-Billiton Research award,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nstf.org.za/wp-content/uploads/2017/06/13WinnersPressRelease.pdf|title=NSTF Winners Press Release|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref> [[South African Medical Research Council|MRC]] Scientific Achievement Award (Gold), and is a South African [[National Research Foundation of South Africa|National Research Foundation]] A-rated scientist.<ref name="NRF A rated scientist">{{cite web|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=NRF A rated scientist|url=https://www.news.uct.ac.za/article/-2017-12-15-new-nrf-a-rating-for-keertan-dheda|website=uct.ac.za|publisher=University of Cape Town|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> He has been profiled in [[The Lancet]],<ref name="The Lancet: Rising star of pulmonary medicine">{{cite journal|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=Rising star of pulmonology|journal=The Lancet|volume=383|issue=9915|page=403|doi=10.1016/S0140-6736(14)60140-9|pmid=24485575|url=https://www.thelancet.com/journals/lancet/article/PIIS0140-6736(14)60140-9/fulltext|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> the [[Business Day (South Africa)|Business Day]] newspaper,<ref>{{cite web|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=Man on a mission|url=https://www.pressreader.com/south-africa/business-day/20140630/281719792675888|website=Pressreader.com|publisher=Press Reader|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> [[Independent Online (South Africa)|IOL]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.iol.co.za/capetimes/news/uct-to-spearhead-research-into-antibiotic-resistance-15838172|title=UCT to spearhead research into antibiotic resistance {{!}} Cape Times|access-date=2018-07-05|language=en}}</ref> [[News24]],<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.news24.com/SouthAfrica/News/tb-bomb-set-to-expolde-20170226-2|title=TB bomb set to expolde|work=News24|access-date=2018-07-05|language=en}}</ref> and [[Carte Blanche (TV series)|Carte Blanche]], a high-profile news programme in South Africa.
== Leadership == He serves on the editorial board of the journals [[PLOS One|PLoS One]], [[American Journal of Respiratory and Critical Care Medicine|American Journal of Respiratory and Critical Medicine]], [[The Lancet|Lancet Respiratory Diseases]] and [[Scientific Reports]], amongst others. He serves on several national and international academic and advisory bodies and holds 5 patents. He is the current President of the [https://pulmonology.co.za/ South African Thoracic Society],<ref name="President of South African Thoracic Society">{{cite web|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=President of South African Thoracic Society|url=http://pulmonology.co.za/council-members/|website=pulmonology.co.za|publisher=South African Thoracic Society|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> and is the founder and co-director of the charity, [https://www.freeoftb.com/ Free of TB],<ref name="Founder and director of Free of TB">{{cite web|last1=Dheda|first1=Keertan|title=Director and founder of Free of TB charity|url=http://www.freeoftb.com|website=freeoftb.com|publisher=Free of TB|accessdate=29 May 2018}}</ref> which provides support and healthcare to poor and needy persons afflicted with TB.
