'''Maitri Pune''' is a volunteer [[non-governmental organisation]] based in [[Pune]], India whose work includes helping [[tribals]] in the [[Melghat]] and [[Marathwada]] regions. They have helped to lower the infant mortality rate, along with raising agricultural production and increasing AIDS awareness. In recent years they have expanded their reach to include natural disaster relief and a helpline for AIDS awareness which was receiving 1,500 calls a day as of 2009.<ref name="TOI">{{cite news|url=http://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2009-05-19/pune/28175518_1_melghat-region-aids-awareness-engineering-student|title=With Maitri, weekends get a new meaning|last=Anand|first=Shambhavi|author2=Samarpita Banerjee|date=2009-05-19|work=Times of India|accessdate=15 January 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=196533|title=Appeal for Aid|date=08-12-2006|work=Express India|accessdate=15 January 2011|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071111164503/http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=196533#|archive-date=11 November 2007|dead-url=yes|df=dmy-all}}</ref>

